title: Grateful Dead Live at Ventura County Fairgrounds on 1982-07-18
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1/Dolby B) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> Samplitude Professional v10.22 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried > Mexicali Blues, Loser, Cassidy, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain > Deal

Set 2

Samson And Delilah > Franklin's Tower, Women Are Smarter, Ship Of Fools, Crazy Fingers > Drums > Not Fade Away > Wharf Rat > Sugar Magnolia

E: (I Can't Get No) Satisfaction > Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Love This Loser I must be missing something here. I have heard this version of Loser probably 100 times and I can't for the life of me figure out what is "horrendous" about it. I actually really like it and Loser is one of my favorite tunes. I think the solo is great and Phil punctuates it with a serious bass run. And I am not one of those heads who thinks everything they did was great. I saw plenty of shows and some were clunkers, but I like the Loser and Crazy Fingers from this show very much. I just don't get it. To each his own I guess.

If I had a Gun.... Hmmm, weird review RE "horrendous Loser." Late night and I pulled this up just to hear the Loser!!
Agree w other poster, its smashing, raucous and Phil goes off at the peak of a killer solo. Seemed like they were really getting after it and having fun!

To each his/her own...peace

Don't forget Fingers breakout either! 35 years ago

My oh my This show cooks in every way. If your checking it out for 1st time you will not be disappointed at all.  
 They came to play on this tour and pulled out Crazy fingers from there bag of tricks.  Yes the Loser kicks ass , so does the rest of the show. After these shows we were lucky to get a copy sum time later during the summer tour and we for sure played the heck out of it.
 Gets 100 stars for the scene sound and feel as if your still there. 
 GREAT job on the recording guys.
